 The animal , aptly named Hagrid after the fictional giant in Harry Potter was born on Tuesday at three times the size of its peers .
Dwarfing other newborns on the farm in Gelston near Grantham in Lincolnshire where he was born , owners believe he may be the biggest ever lamb born in the UK at 25 lbs .
The lamb was born naturally on Tuesday and his mother is in remarkably good condition .